According to the latest Radio Africa monthly opinion poll, 47.1 per cent of respondents say they would vote for DP William Ruto if the presidential election were held today, compared to 35.1 percent for Raila Odinga. Other potential presidential contenders appear to be a long way off, according to the poll. Kalonzo Musyoka has 1.5 percent support; Musalia Mudavadi 1.1 percent support; and 'Others' 1.9 percent. Another 7.8 per cent were undecided while 2.8 percent said they would not vote and 2.4 percent refused to answer.